Title: Relates to requirements for certain mental health practitioners to be issued privilege to diagnose and develop assessment-based treatment plans
Summary: Provides alternate education and experience requirements for mental health counselors, marriage and family therapists, and psychoanalysts licensed prior to 06/24/2027, to be issued privilege to diagnose and develop assessment-based treatment plans; lowers fees for such diagnostic privileges to $100.
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the education law, in relation to requirements for certain mental health practitioners to be issued privilege to diagnose and develop assessment-based treatment plans
